PN,41908
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F419A1780650345
OL,3,CMan pleads guilty to violent disorder
OL,4,Cin Southampton after Henry Nowak murder
OL,6,FThe protest followed the sentencing of
OL,7,FVickrum Digwa, 23, to life
OL,8,Fimprisonment to serve a minimum of 21
OL,9,Fyears for the murder of 18-year-old Mr
OL,10,FNowak in December.
OL,12,FAnger erupted after police body-worn
OL,13,Fvideo was released showing Mr Nowak
OL,14,Fbeing placed in handcuffs moments
OL,15,Fbefore he became unconscious and
OL,16,Fsubsequently died.
OL,18,FThe trial heard that Digwa had lied to
OL,19,Fpolice attending the scene by saying
OL,20,Fhe had been racially abused by Mr
OL,21,FNowak and denying he had stabbed him.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G8/11
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
